keystore driver

DEVICES:
misc: /dev/keystore - keystore interface


 * make all

 * default and all
 * make TRACE=y - enable excessive print outs
 * make DEBUG=n - disable verbose debug output

INSTALLATION:
 * run in root privileged make install
   - (e.g) sudo make install
 * NOTE: no need to install in development work mode

LOADING:
 * modprobe keystore or insmod ./keystore.ko
 * (DEVELOPMENT MODE) ./scripts/reload.sh - unload (if loaded) and load the driver

REMOVING:
 * modprobe -r keystore
 * (DEVELOPMENT MODE) ./scripts/unload.sh

INFO:
 * debug messages are displayed in dmesg or /var/log/messages

DEVELOPMENT SCRIPTS:
 * ./scripts/install.sh
 * ./scripts/load.sh
 * ./scripts/reload.sh
 * ./scripts/unload.sh
 * ./scripts/test.sh
 * ./scripts/version.sh
